; Regression test for issue #1793: Unexpected balance report when tracking food calories
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1793
; BUG: C commodity conversion directive ignores the quantity on the left side.
; "C 100 apple = 48 kcal" should mean 1 apple = 0.48 kcal (225 apple → 108 kcal),
; but ledger treats it as 1 apple = 48 kcal (225 apple → 10800 kcal), off by 100x.

commodity apple
commodity sugar

C 100 apple = 48 kcal
C 100 sugar = 400 kcal

payee Food

account Food:Fruits
account Food:Other
account Source:Pantry

2019-05-19 Food
    Food:Fruits  225 apple
    Food:Other  8 sugar
    Source:Pantry

test bal
          14000 kcal  Food
          10800 kcal    Fruits
           3200 kcal    Other
         -14000 kcal  Source:Pantry
--------------------
                   0
end test
